 Not really sure, but....
 
 If you think you have a good game, what does it hurt to send a DEMO version
 to numerous magazines for potential review.  You could also mention you are
 looking for someone to distribute (if that is what you want to do) your game.
 If it makes it in a magazine and gets a good review, potential distributors
 may come knocking at your door.  And if you have the resourses to ditribute
 yourself, and you passed this information on to the magazines, hopefully 
 people will send directly to you.
 
 If you have addresses for known game developing houses, you could also
 send demos directly to them.  What could it hurt?
 
 Hope this helps.
 
 Sincerely
 
 Tom Stone (the guy who wrote Fantasy Quest for the Mac and then made it
